This is what you'll wear when I finish dyeing it.

82
00:09:19,090 --> 00:09:23,410
That's Dudley's old uniform. It'll fit like old elephant skin.

83
00:09:23,570 --> 00:09:25,850
Fit you well enough.

84
00:09:26,170 --> 00:09:29,810
Go get the post. Go!

85
00:09:59,730 --> 00:10:02,410
Marge is ill. Ate a funny whelk.

86
00:10:02,610 --> 00:10:05,810
- Dad, look! Harry's got a letter! - It's mine!

87
00:10:06,010 --> 00:10:08,770
Yours? Who'd be writing to you?

88
00:10:40,050 --> 00:10:44,610
No more mail through this letterbox.

89
00:11:30,270 --> 00:11:33,110
Have a lovely day at the office, dear.

90
00:11:35,990 --> 00:11:38,670
Shoo! Go on.

91
00:12:03,510 --> 00:12:06,390
Fine day, Sunday.

92
00:12:07,030 --> 00:12:11,710
In my opinion, best day of the week. Why is that, Dudley?

93
00:12:11,910 --> 00:12:16,350
- Because there's no post on Sundays? - Right you are, Harry!

94
00:12:16,550 --> 00:12:19,310
No post on Sunday.

95
00:12:20,710 --> 00:12:24,630
No blasted letters today! No, sir.

96
00:12:25,230 --> 00:12:30,190
Not one single bloody letter. Not one!

97
00:12:38,590 --> 00:12:42,470
No, sir, not one blasted, miserable...

98
00:12:53,990 --> 00:12:56,190
Make it stop, please!

