175
00:20:27,060 --> 00:20:30,380
All students must be equipped with

176
00:20:30,580 --> 00:20:33,500
one standard size 2 pewter cauldron

177
00:20:33,700 --> 00:20:36,600
and may bring, if they desire,

178
00:20:36,600 --> 00:20:39,500
either an owl, a cat or a toad.

179
00:20:39,740 --> 00:20:42,340
Can we find all this in London?

180
00:20:42,540 --> 00:20:44,940
If you know where to go.

181
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:10,660
Ah, Hagrid! The usual, I presume?

182
00:21:10,860 --> 00:21:14,740
No, thanks, Tom. I'm on official Hogwarts business.

183
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:18,060
Just helping Harry buy his school supplies.

184
00:21:18,300 --> 00:21:21,860
Bless my soul. It's Harry Potter!

185
00:21:26,140 --> 00:21:29,580
Welcome back, Mr. Potter. Welcome back.

186
00:21:29,820 --> 00:21:34,140
Doris Crockford. I can't believe I'm meeting you at last.

187
00:21:34,620 --> 00:21:39,860
Harry Potter. Can't tell you how pleased I am to meet you.

188
00:21:40,060 --> 00:21:42,620
Hello, professor. I didn't see you.

189
00:21:42,760 --> 00:21:44,620
Harry, this is Professor Quirrell.

190
00:21:42,820 --> 00:21:47,720
He will be teaching your Defense Against the Dark Arts teacher at Hogwarts.

191
00:21:48,020 --> 00:21:50,460
Oh, nice to meet you.

192
00:21:50,700 --> 00:21:53,780
Fearfully fascinating subject.

193
00:21:53,980 --> 00:21:58,620
Not that you need it, eh, Potter?

194
00:21:59,540 --> 00:22:03,700
